content.description: Climb arete right of La Vida Loca's second pitch.
Three pitches, crux 11c on second pitch. Great moves over a roof on last pitch.

walk @ 150 yds south of EGG on ledge to huge light green arete. Climb past 6 bolts and 3 small nuts to the chain anchors on a small ledge for pitch 1 (5.8). Climb both sides of the arete on the second pitch, past 7 bolts and pro to a large green ledge(crux pitch). 1st 2 pitches combine nicely for 190ft enduro pitch. Finish on an easy crack to top. Rappel route with a 60m rope.

climbs.name: Vitamin M
climbs.fa: M. Rangel, J. Garcia, et al

content.description: Just right of Doubts Even Here (5.9 crack) is a roof with a couple tough liebacks.  The crux is getting past the second small roof. Rest on a ledge and saunter up the last bolt to the anchor at base of Gone Grey.
L of Vagina Envy, R of Further. roof to crack to steep head wall. 115ft to anchors.

3 pitch Chimney adventure left of No white Flag: 5.7 beautiful hands up the left side of the chimney 100ft, 5.9 varied cracks to ledge 60ft, 5.6 chimney tunnel up & through the hole 100ft. (watch for loose talus in the bottom of this chimney) possible to do just the first pitch then diagonally up and Left to rap off Vertical Addiction anchors 110ft.

This route goes up and right from the wide crack on face to a great #2 camalot placement out right.  Up steeper rock to a wide easy flakey area then the arching dihedral/roof.  Pass this to easy rock, save the 2nd #2 camalot for the finish.
content.protection: standard rack, lots of finger-sized gear.
content.location: Just 10 yds right of No White Flag; look for a low roof with huge blocks below it on the ledge trail 205 yds past the fixed line overhang.  Shares a start with The Gambler.  This line goes right on the horizontal holds to a crack going up and left to exit out a hand crack roof.  Great finish, good rock.

climbs.name: Slate's Day Off
climbs.fa: A. Marquardt, B. Mattingly, M. Rangel

content.description: The crux is above the ledge near the 5th bolt.
content.location: This is the climb starting on the arete above the ledge trail, just 10 yds south of the Great Race arete.  Climb up to the oak ledge and continue to the chains.

content.description: steep face, stay on easy ground in dihedral, passing 2 bolts to a steep slightly overhung offset crack that widens from a seam to hands.
content.protection: 2 bolts, nuts and cams to #3; chain anchor on ledge.

content.description: 100 yards south on Green Wall's ledge to the large low angle crack at the end. Meander 200' up ledges and incipient cracks. Stay right of the gully.

Starts directly above the cold-shut bolted belay of Everything's Gone Green. Climb easy 5.7 on gear for first 35 ft. to first bolt above ledge. difficult onsight but w/ the right beta both roofs go easy 11. You can bail right at the last roof if you're too pumped and climb past the little tree. Rap 100' from two cold shuts (one 60m rope) to E.G.G anchors. Watch the ends of your rope on this rap! 60m rope just touches ledge.
content.protection: Eight bolts to two bolt belay at top of buttress. Plus pro to #1 Camalot for start.

content.description: This is the finger crack left of Semper Fi, good fingers and occasional tight hands to the end of the crack then the difficulty begins at the bolts.
content.location: Just left of Semper Fi; rap route from chains.

content.description: Getting established on the steep start is difficult, then the final clip is a tad far, but clipping off a jug.  That is pitch one.  The next pitch is the crux, move off a good right hand to a tips sidepull and a high left foot made this an awkward rock over.  Then a difficult finish to boot.
content.protection: 10 bolts to climb to top (if you climb the third pitch of Warhippies)
content.location: From the ledge/trail next to Great Race, 4th class to the large Oak/ledge above and look for bolts right of Warhippies.

content.description: Walk south along ledge, just before Vagina Envy's chimney is an overhanging face with a roof at the top. First bolt is @ 15' up on easy rock; crux is small holds and a tips crack move.

climbs.name: Need Em Brain
climbs.fa: M. Rangel, Brian Nedom, Patrick MacLane

content.description: Mostly fingers and smaller cracks with a single bolt @ 50' up.  A tricky bulge is passed on the right near the end of pitch 1.  Belay on ledge w/piton and gear.  Pitch two heads up wider cracks, when crack gets a bit broken above another ledge, look left for great crack/pro to top.  Finishes on wider crack w/chockstone.  Walk right to Walking Dead Arete's anchor.
content.protection: lots of small wires, double small C3 to #2 camalots, single #3, #4 camalot, sling for chockstone near top, one bolt, one piton.
content.location: Left of Walking Dead Arete and Gear and Moaning, look for single bolt in brown stain.  Rap WDA w/single 60m

content.description: Climb a rocky dihedral (sling the chockstone low for added fun) and climb out left onto a face after placing a stopper. Continue up to a bolt and then to a hand crack with some nice face holds on the right. Shares the same shuts as The Proposal. Rap down to the base of the proposal and walk back to your packs around the corner.
content.protection: Small stoppers, friends up to #3 and a draw for the bolt. Bring a few slings.
content.location: If heading south on the ledges, pass the proposal and continue for 20-30 feet and the start is on the right.

content.description: Description: Face and cracks on east-facing arete of the huge buttress located L of Transmission. Clip the first bolt then natural pro and more bolts to a body length roof (crux) for pitch 1; 4th class 40' to gain the top of the buttress and the anchors for Remission. Pitch 3 begins in a crack on the belay ledge. Bolts and pro bring you to a 5' roof split by a crack in the center. Climb above the roof on natural pro to the anchor.
just left of Friend of the Devil (shares the same anchor) steep thin arete, 80ft
big imposing OW/Chimney w/ adjacent orange and yellow faces is accessed from ledge left of Walking Dead Arete's 2nd pitch. easier and more fun than you'd expect. leads to summit rim.
content.protection: one bolt plus standard rack to #4.

content.description: Climb Everything Gone Green and move belay 30' right. start under double crack alcove with roof. Aim for the grey tree at the top of the route. Solid crack and great protection all the way.

This is the wide crack just 10 yds right of No White Flag (12a sport).  It shares a start with Snake on a Tree (11a trad)but it continues up and left through a bombay chimney then a squeeze then a wide crack through a small roof.  Latter being the crux, just stem, it'll be fine.
content.protection: standard rack of camalots, double 4,5 and a 6 friend for the bombay chimney down low.
content.location: From No White Flag, go right @ 10 yds to a wide crack below a low roof with huge blocks on the ground beneath it.

content.description: Just left of Walking Dead Arete is a crack system that shoots straight to the top. Climb thin cracks and face to final headwall with 3 bolts to top of 2nd pitch of WDA. Route is 190' long, rap twice w/single 60m rope.
content.protection: thin pro: RPs to #2 camalot, 5 bolts

content.description: fURTHER takes you 180ft past a roof then up a blunt arete to a ledge above the great roof. 2nd pitch:80ft: 5.9 finger to hand crack above anchors for "Closer". Rap single rope down Closer's anchors.
Stellar hands and fingers starting at a juggy roof. Ends 85' later at a small tree on a ledge.

This route is the last route on the face with EGG.  It is before you get to the gully that separates this face from the Walking Dead Arete. 

  You start in an alcove under a roof.  Work your way up to the roof with a few face mores and some stemming.  Exit the roof to the right, work you way up the face to another roof, exit right again, then proceed to the top via easier and easily protectable terrain.  Shares bolted anchor with EGG and DEH.
content.protection: Standard rack, nothing bigger than a #3 C4.

content.description: Analog to Remission, it is the wide south crack that splits the buttress at the north end of the green wall.
This starts thin on great face with a thin crack.  Located just right of EGG; this has a wide spot above, save a couple wide pieces for this.  Great rock.

Great route of four continuous pitches. Lots of solid gear as often as you want and fun technical climbing (face, stemming, semi-chimning, crack, etc.) About 350' and the ratings are 5.6, 5.8, 5.9, 5.6
corner/crack system immediately right of Redneck Protestor takes you to the same anchors.
Main staging area that extends from La Vida Loca on the right to the fixed traverse line on the left.
